{"word":"θρῆνος","slug":"θρῆνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θρῆνος</b></el> <el>(θρῆνος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θρέομαι'><el>θρέομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a funeral-song, dirge, lament</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>naenia</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>θρῆνος οὑμός</el> <i>for</i> me, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a complaint, sad strain</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}